{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTag","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudstag"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTag"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Indicators"],"kind":"mentions"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Appearances","anchor":"Appearances","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tags have two appearances so as to highlight or not their content:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"emphasized","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": A tag with a solid, high-contrast background. Used to draw strong attention to important"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"labels or categories. Emphasized tags stand out prominently against the interface and are ideal for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"primary or high-priority information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"muted","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": A tag with a subtle, light, or semi-transparent background. Used for secondary or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"less prominent information. Muted tags blend more with the background, providing a softer visual","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"emphasis compared to emphasized tags.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Status","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Status"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Tags have seven status depending on the context of the information they represent. Each state is designed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to convey a specific meaning and ensure clarity in communication.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Neutral"}]},{"text":": Default or inactive state. Used for standard labels, categories, or when no specific","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"status needs to be communicated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Accent"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Used to draw attention to new features, recommendations, or content suggestions.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Invites users to explore and engage with new offerings, creating an exciting and engaging experience.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Positive","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Indicates success, confirmation, or a positive status. Commonly used to highlight","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"completed actions or approved items.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Warning","type":"text"}]},{"text":": Signals caution or a potentially risky situation. Used to draw attention to items","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requiring user awareness or intervention.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Negative"}]},{"text":": Represents errors, critical issues, or urgent attention needed. Used to highlight","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"problems or failed actions.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Info","type":"text"}]},{"text":": Conveys informational messages or supplementary details. Used for neutral, helpful,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or contextual information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Disabled","type":"text"}]},{"text":": Shows that the tag is inactive and cannot be interacted with. Appears faded or greyed out. This is not","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"allowed when loader is activated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Shape","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Shape"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tags can have two shapes:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rounded","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A tag with fully rounded corners, creating a pill-shaped appearance. Rounded"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tags offer a softer and more approachable look, suitable for most modern interfaces."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Square"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": A tag with sharp, square corners. Squared tags provide a more formal, structured, or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"technical feel. They are often used in business contexts to label promotions, offers, or important notices.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Size","anchor":"Size"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Tags can have two sizes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Default"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The standard tag size, suitable for most use cases and offering good readability.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Small"}]},{"text":": A compact tag with reduced height and font size. Used when saving space is important or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when grouping elements visually.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Layout","anchor":"Layout"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are four available layouts for tags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Text only"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A tag that displays only text. Used for simple labels, categories, or keywords without additional visual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"elements."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Text + Bullet","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A tag with a small indicator (dot) alongside the text. Used to show status, presence, or activity"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"next to the label."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Text + Icon"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A tag that includes an icon before the text. Used to visually reinforce the meaning of the tag,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as status, type, or action."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Text + Loader","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A tag that combines a loading spinner (or progress indicator) with text. Used to indicate that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a process or action related to the tag is in progress."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples"},{"code":["    \/\/ Text only with neutral status, for emphasized appearance with rounded shape in default size","    OUDSTag(label: \"Label\",  status: .neutral(), appearance: .emphasized, shape: .rounded, size: .default)","    \/\/ Or also","    OUDSTag(label: \"Label\")","    \/\/ Or from a localizale and a bundle","    OUDSTag(LocalizedStringKey(\"label_wording\"), bundle: Bundle.module)","","    \/\/ Tag with neutral status with bullet","    OUDSTag(label: \"Label\", status: .neutral(leading: .bullet)","","    \/\/ Tag with neutral status with a custom decorative icon","    OUDSTag(label: \"Label\", status: .neutral(icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\")))","    \/\/ If your layout is in RTL mode but your tag has an icon with another meaning because of bad orientation,","    \/\/ you can flip the icon","    OUDSTag(label: \"Label\", status: .neutral(icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"), flipIcon: true))","","    \/\/ Text with neutral status with bullet","    OUDSTag(label: \"Label\", status: .neutral(bullet: true))","","    \/\/ Tag with loader with rounded shape in small size","    OUDSTag(loadingLabel: \"Label\", shape: .rounded, size: .small)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-tag"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tag_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tag_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Sosh"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tag_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_tag_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"1.4.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Version"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.18.0","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Since"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"OUDSTag","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTag"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents7OUDSTagV","symbolKind":"struct","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"15.0","deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false,"unavailable":false},{"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"16.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"11.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSTag","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Structure"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tag is a UI element that allows to display short info like a label, keyword, or category."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Tag helps users quickly find, group, or understand content."}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTag\/Status"],"anchor":"Structures"},{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTag\/init(_:tableName:bundle:status:appearance:shape:size:hasLoader:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponent